name: Anthropic
description: Anthropic conducts AI research and develops AI products, including the Claude AI model family. The company focuses on building AI for human well-being, emphasizing safety in its research, policy work, and product design. Anthropic offers various Claude models, such as Opus and Sonnet, for AI-powered applications and custom experiences, supporting coding and AI agents.
short_description: Anthropic is an AI research company that focuses on the safety and alignment of AI systems with human values.
founders: Daniela Amodei,Dario Amodei,Jack Clark,Jared Kaplan,Sam McCandlish,Tom Brown

name: Perplexity
description: Perplexity is a answer engine that utilizes artificial intelligence (AI) to integrate large language models and search engines. The platform utilizes natural language processing (NLP) and generative AI technologies to provide conversational responses to user queries. The platform is designed to bridge the gap between traditional search engines and AI-driven interactive assistance.
short_description: Perplexity is an AI-powered answer engine designed to provide accurate, real-time responses to user queries.
categories: Artificial Intelligence (AI),Chatbot,Machine Learning,Natural Language Processing,Search Engine

name: ElevenLabs
description: ElevenLabs is an AI company that offers tools for speech synthesis, voice cloning, dubbing, and audio generation. It provides platforms for creating and deploying voice agents, generating expressive speech in dozens of languages, and localizing content at scale. Its services include a developer API, creative tools for content creators, and solutions for enterprises to integrate AI voice into applications. The company also supports features like voice design, voice isolation, and audio effects. It enables clients to convert text into realistic speech, clone voices from short samples, and translate spoken content while retaining tone and emotion.
short_description: ElevenLabs is an AI company that offers tools for speech synthesis, voice cloning, dubbing, and audio generation.

name: Harvey
description: Harvey offers AI-powered solutions designed to streamline legal work for law firms and corporate legal teams. Its tools support tasks such as document review, contract analysis, legal research, and due diligence, helping professionals save time and improve accuracy. The platform uses natural language processing to interpret complex legal language and generate relevant insights. Harvey’s services are tailored to meet the specific needs of clients across various practice areas.
short_description: Harvey provides AI-driven tools to assist legal professionals with research, document review, and contract analysis.

name: Chainguard
description: Chainguard provides hardened, minimal container images that are continuously rebuilt from source in secure environments, aiming to eliminate known vulnerabilities and ensure end-to-end integrity. These images come with built-in cryptographic signatures, Software Bill of Materials (SBOMs), and Supply-chain Levels for Software Artifacts (SLSA) provenance. In addition to container images, Chainguard offers a catalog of guarded Java dependencies through its Chainguard Libraries, built securely from source in SLSA-certified infrastructure. The company also contributes to and maintains several widely used open source projects, reflecting its commitment to the open source community.
short_description: Chainguard is a cloud-native development platform that provides low-to-zero CVE container images for building and running applications.

name: Fireworks AI
description: Fireworks AI provides a cloud-based platform that enables developers and enterprises to run, fine-tune and deploy open-source large language, vision and multimodal models through a low-latency inference engine. The company offers serverless infrastructure that handles model lifecycle management from development to production, and gives users access to a library of pre-optimised models alongside the ability to customise models for their own data and use cases. Through partnerships with leading GPU and cloud hardware providers, Fireworks AI supports high throughput, reduced latency and scalable deployments without requiring customers to provision or manage their own infrastructure. The platform addresses the challenge of converting prototype AI models into operational applications by combining infrastructure optimisation, developer tools and enterprise-grade compliance.
short_description: Fireworks AI is an advanced platform that enables users to build, tune, and scale AI applications using open-source models

name: Anysphere
description: Anysphere is an applied research lab focused on automating coding processes. The company develops software and models to create a human-AI programmer, aiming for a significant increase in programming effectiveness. This hybrid approach allows for faster iteration and control over complex codebases.
short_description: Anysphere is an applied research lab focused on automating coding through innovative AI solutions.
categories: Artificial Intelligence (AI),Developer Tools,Generative AI,Machine Learning,Software Engineering

name: Mercor
description: Mercor presents an AI-powered platform that helps connect domain experts with roles in AI and other tech disciplines. It supports sourcing, vetting, and payment for talent, offering remote, expert-level assignments across fields like software engineering, consulting, data and legal. Additionally, the platform includes an interview preparation section where candidates can access hundreds of expert-reviewed mock interviews in areas such as software, design, security and analytics. Mercor uses machine-driven interview tools to assess candidate performance, aiming to streamline how expertise is matched to project work.
short_description: Mercor is an AI-based hiring platform that improves the recruitment process by matching talent with opportunities tailored to their skills.

name: Scribe
description:
Scribe helps organizations capture and optimize how work gets done. 

Their Workflow AI platform turns processes into living playbooks to train colleagues, assist customers, and drive software adoption. 

Scribe Capture automatically creates and shares step-by-step guides, complete with text and screenshots — no more manual documentation.

Scribe Optimize helps your organization understand how to make work better. It continuously mines workflows to identify the biggest opportunities to improve and turns those insights into data-backed recommendations, with customized business cases to drive the highest ROI transformation.

Trusted by teams at New York Life, T-Mobile, LinkedIn, HubSpot, and Northern Trust, Scribe is used by 94% of the Fortune 500 to work smarter, faster, and deliver exceptional results. Scribe is loved by 5 million users and 600,000 organizations.
short_description: Scribe’s Workflow AI platform helps organizations capture and optimize how work gets done.

name: Figure
description: Figure is an AI robotics company that develops autonomous general-purpose humanoid robots to address labor shortages and reduce the number of workers in unsafe jobs. It also develops commercially viable autonomous humanoid robots that lend support across manufacturing, logistics, warehousing, and retail.
short_description: Figure is an AI robotics company that develops autonomous general-purpose humanoid robots.

name: Glean
description:
Glean develops an AI-based search engine software that connects enterprise data and generates answers through a tool in any company. It provides an AI assistant and enterprise search platform called Workplace Search that connects to internal data sources to help employees find information and answer questions. 

The platform uses advanced search, retrieval, augmented generation, and large language models to generate personalized answers grounded in.
short_description: Glean develops an AI-based search engine software that connects enterprise data and generates answers to improve workplace efficiency.
categories: Artificial Intelligence (AI),Enterprise Software,Generative AI,Machine Learning,Search Engine
founders: Arvind Jain,Piyush Prahladka,Prafful Goel,Sharvanath Pathak,Tony Gentilcore,TR Vishwanath

name: Metsera
description: Metsera is a biotechnology company that develops and manufactures therapies. The company's focus is on nutrient-stimulated hormone therapies for obesity and related conditions. Its portfolio includes both injectable and oral therapeutic candidates.
short_description: Metsera is a clinical‐stage biotech firm developing oral & injectable hormone therapies to treat obesity & related metabolic diseases.

name: Suno
description: Suno is a music start-up that enables anyone to make the songs they want. The company aims to help people rediscover the joy of play and exploration.
short_description: Suno is a music start-up that enables anyone to make the songs they want.

name: Cipher Mining
description: Cipher Mining is an industrial-scale Bitcoin mining company dedicated to expanding and strengthening the Bitcoin network's critical infrastructure. Its goal is to be the leading Bitcoin mining company in the United States. Cipher Mining aims to leverage best-in-class technology, market-leading power purchase arrangements, and a seasoned, dedicated senior management team to become the market leader in Bitcoin mining.
short_description: Cipher Mining is an industrial-scale Bitcoin mining company dedicated to expanding and strengthening the Bitcoin network's infrastructure.

name: Character.ai
description: Character.ai provides open-ended conversational applications in which users create characters and converse with them. The company aims to create dialogue agents with a broad range of uses in entertainment, instruction, general question-answering, and other areas. The business specializes in neural language models, which can be used as tools for creativity, idea generation, language learning, and a variety of other tasks. Users can access dialogue agents that are propelled by in-house technology.
short_description: Character.ai provides open-ended conversational applications in which users create characters and converse with them.

name: Bullish
description: Bullish is a regulated and audited global cryptocurrency exchange that allows users to securely buy, sell, and trade digital assets. The platform is designed with an emphasis on institutional finance, offering market infrastructure and information services in the cryptocurrency sector.
short_description: Bullish is a regulated and audited global cryptocurrency exchange that allows users to securely buy, sell, and trade digital assets.

name: Sublime Security
description: Sublime Security is the adaptive, AI-powered cloud email security platform that combines effectiveness with visibility and control. The open platform allows security teams to have transparency and flexibility in their email environment to spend less time on email-originated incidents. Advanced teams can customize detections, threat hunt, extend Sublime into their SIEM or SOAR, and collaborate with other teams.
short_description: Sublime Security develops an email security platform to write and run custom detection and response rules to block phishing attacks.

name: Windsurf
description:
Windsurf offers an AI coding assistant designed to enhance developers' productivity. The platform features an integrated development environment that simplifies coding tasks and streamlines workflows. It supports multiple operating systems, including Mac, Windows, and Linux, making it accessible to a wide range of users. 

Windsurf provides a free version for individual developers, while teams can access additional features through an enterprise offering. This flexibility allows users to choose the option that best suits their needs. 

By focusing on usability and functionality, Windsurf aims to improve its users' overall coding experience.
short_description: Windsurf provides an AI coding assistant and an integrated development environment for developers.

name: ShopMy
description: ShopMy is a creator-centric ecosystem that links top brands with influential creators to facilitate partnerships. The platform offers tools for creating digital shops, managing affiliate links, and building brand relationships, enabling creators to monetize their content effectively.
short_description: ShopMy connects brands and creators for seamless partnership and monetization.

name: Cyera
description: Cyera is a data security company that gives businesses deep context on their data, applying proper, continuous controls to assure cyber-resilience and compliance. Cyera takes a data-centric approach to security across your data landscape, empowering security teams to know where their data is, and what exposes it to risk, and take immediate action to remediate exposures. Backed by leading investors, including Sequoia, Accel, Cyberstarts, and Redpoint Ventures, Cyera is redefining how companies secure data in the cloud.
short_description: Cyera is an AI-powered data security platform that gives enterprises deep context on their data to assure cyber-resilience and compliance.
categories: Artificial Intelligence (AI),Cloud Data Services,Cyber Security,Network Security

name: Lava
description: Lava is a bitcoin lending platform that offers a self-custodial wallet for managing bitcoin finances.
short_description: Lava is a bitcoin lending platform that offers a self-custodial wallet for managing bitcoin finances.

name: Vivo
description: Vivo offers an online and interactive fitness program designed specifically for seniors. Seniors can do it all from home on their laptop or mobile device with a live certified trainer.
short_description: Vivo offers an online and interactive fitness program designed specifically for seniors.

name: EvenUp
description: EvenUp develops artificial intelligence software that automates the preparation of legal demand packages for personal injury cases. The company’s platform reviews medical records, police reports, and other case documents to generate detailed settlement demands that reflect the full impact of injuries and losses. EvenUp’s technology assists law firms by identifying relevant case details, calculating damages, and drafting comprehensive narratives that support fair compensation outcomes. Its system streamlines repetitive administrative tasks, helping legal professionals focus on strategy and advocacy rather than document assembly. Through this process, EvenUp helps standardize and improve the accuracy of settlement documentation within personal injury law practices.
short_description: EvenUp is a legal tech company developing AI software that automates the preparation of legal demand packages for personal injury cases.

name: Sierra
description: Sierra provides a platform that builds and manages conversational AI agents for businesses. The agents are deployed on multiple channels, including voice, to answer customer questions and solve problems. The platform allows companies to ground an agent with their own knowledge and processes.
short_description: Sierra provides a platform that builds and manages conversational AI agents for customer experiences.

name: Flex
description: Flex is a financial technology company that offers an end-to-end finance platform that integrates business and personal finance management. Their services include business banking with zero monthly fees, 1% cashback on eligible purchases, and high-yield accounts with up to 2.99% APY on idle cash. They provide a business credit card featuring 0% interest for 60 days on eligible purchases, unlimited cashback, and flexible rewards. Flex also offers accounts payable automation with features like fraud prevention, AI-powered bill scanning, and real-time payment tracking. Additionally, their platform supports global payments across over 180 countries in 32 currencies, catering to businesses with international operations.
short_description: Flex is a financial technology company that offers an end-to-end finance platform that integrates business and personal finance management.

name: Campfire
description:
Campfire offers an AI-native enterprise resource planning software for mid-sized and enterprise companies. It delivers two integrated modules: Core Accounting, a modern general ledger that streamlines month-end closes, supports multi-entity and currency consolidations, and unlocks real-time financial insights; and Revenue Automation, which manages invoicing, billing, revenue recognition, and deferred revenue workflows—all from a unified system. The platform provides embedded Ember AI chat for conversational financial reporting, bank reconciliation, and workflow automation via multi-API integrations.

Campfire simplifies audit-ready processes with locked periods, contract databases, and comprehensive audit trails. By combining scalable architecture with an API-first design, it enables finance teams to close faster, elevate reporting, and support global operations with visibility and efficiency.
short_description: Campfire offers an AI-native enterprise resource planning software for mid-sized and enterprise companies.

name: Genspark
description: Genspark offers an AI workspace that helps users streamline a wide range of tasks through a single prompt. The platform delivers tools such as AI Slides, AI Sheets, AI Docs, AI Chat, AI Image, and AI Video, all integrated to support workflow creation from document and data import to content generation and automation. It utilizes a “Mixture-of-Agents” architecture that orchestrates multiple specialized models alongside a toolset of over 80 professional utilities to perform actions such as research synthesis, slide generation, phone call automation, and web navigation. Users can prompt Genspark to analyze data, build visualizations, draft documents, synthesize information from the web, and generate multimedia content without needing advanced technical setup. By consolidating document, presentation, sheet, chat and image/video capabilities into one interface, Genspark enables users to move from idea to execution within the same environment.
short_description: Genspark is an AI search platform that utilizes generative AI to create custom summaries and detailed overviews in response to user queries.

name: Sage
description: Sage is a next-generation operation management system designed for senior living communities. It provides tools for data collection and analysis, improving caregiver operations and resident care outcomes. The platform streamlines communication and task management, enabling care teams to deliver informed and collaborative support.
short_description: Sage is an operation management system that enhances senior caregiving efficiency.

name: ASP Isotopes
description: ASP Isotopes is a pre-commercial stage advanced materials company that develops isotope enrichment technology for the medical, green energy, and industrial sectors
short_description: ASP Isotopes develops isotope enrichment technology for the medical, green energy, and industrial sectors.

name: Parse Biosciences
description:
Parse Bio is a biotechnology startup company developing single-cell sequencing kit solutions for researchers.

By using combinatorial cDNA barcoding within cells themselves, Parse Biosciences’s technology allows researchers to eliminate the need for complex and expensive microfluidic instruments. Additionally, the company’s technology enables samples to be fixed, frozen, and stored, allowing researchers to separate out the sample extraction from downstream library preparation steps. This capability empowers researchers to run fixed samples collected on different dates together in a single experiment, providing greater control over sample handling and reducing handling errors. Split Biosciences rebranded as Parse Biosciences in 2020.

The Seattle, Washington-based biotech company was established in 2018 by Alex Rosenberg, Charlie Roco, and Georg Friedrich Seelig.
short_description: Parse Biosciences is a biotechnology startup company that develops single-cell sequencing kit solutions for researchers.

name: Beeline
description: Beeline is a developer of a digital home loan lending platform intended to simplify the process of financing.The company uses both artificial intelligence and personal "Loan Guides" to cut down the timing during the home lending process, providing home-buyers and refinancers a solution for more transparency and ease.
short_description: Beeline is a developer of a digital home loan lending platform intended to simplify the process of financing.
founders: Greg Ellis,Jay Stockwell,Jess Kennedy,Nick Liuzza,Peter Gonzalez

name: Roam
description: Roam is a virtual office designed to bring your whole distributed company together in one headquarters. It transforms company productivity with faster, shorter meetings, enhances culture by creating a feeling of presence together, and improves efficiency with an all-in-one app at an affordable price. Roam is the office of tomorrow, available today.
short_description: Roam: A virtual office that boosts productivity, enhances culture, and improves efficiency.
founders: Grace Sutherland,Howard Lerman,Jon Brod,Sean MacIsaac,Tom Dixon

name: Hebbia
description: Hebbia is the interface for AGI– the first AI platform that works the way humans work. Designed to tackle even the most complex tasks, it turns prompts into processes that AI agents complete. Finance, law, government, and pharma professionals from the world’s largest institutions are using Hebbia to execute workflows with hundreds of steps over millions of documents. While other systems are a black box, Hebbia shows its work, letting users verify, trust, and collaborate with AI.
short_description: Hebbia is an AI platform that helps companies transform heaps of information into insights.

name: Truffle Security
description: Truffle Security is a cybersecurity company that offers software solutions for managing private keys and credentials. Their software scans the system environment to identify private keys and credentials and tracks and manages code data that helps prevent potential security breaches before they occur.
short_description: Truffle Security is an open source cybersecurity company that offers solutions for finding and remediating leaked software credentials.

name: Together AI
description: Together AI is a cloud-based platform designed for constructing open-source generative AI and infrastructure for developing AI models. The company contributes cutting-edge open-source research, models, and datasets to push the boundaries of AI forward. Through its decentralized cloud services, developers and researchers at organizations of various scales are empowered to train, refine, and deploy generative AI models.
short_description: Together AI is a cloud-based platform designed for constructing open-source generative AI and infrastructure for developing AI models.
founders: Ce Zhang,Chris Re,Percy Liang,Vipul Ved Prakash

name: WellTheory
description: WellTheory provides a virtual care platform focused on autoimmune and inflammatory health. It delivers personalized nutrition, lifestyle, and root-cause assessments, then matches each member with a multidisciplinary Care Team including dietitians, health coaches, and support coordinators. The company supports users through live coaching sessions, unlimited messaging, educational content, community connection, and advanced testing as needed. For employer and payer customers, it offers an enterprise solution that integrates with existing benefit systems, handles implementation, communications, and reporting, and aims to reduce autoimmune-related medical spend.
short_description: WellTheory is a virtual care platform providing autoimmune and inflammatory conditions care services.

name: Assort Health
description: Assort Health delivers voice AI agents tailored for healthcare call centers, offering automation of appointment-related tasks such as scheduling, rescheduling, cancellations, triage, prescription refills, reminders, and multilingual support. These AI agents interface with clinics’ systems to follow specialty-specific rules, verify patient details, and route calls efficiently. The solution integrates with electronic health record and practice management platforms to support streamlined workflows and reduce call handling burdens. The technology activates quickly and adapts to diverse clinical specialties, helping staff focus on complex patient care instead of routine tasks.
short_description: Assort Health provides voice AI agents designed for healthcare call centers, enabling automation of appointment management tasks.

name: Jasper
description: Jasper is an AI platform specifically designed for marketing, enabling users to generate high-quality content at a significantly faster rate. It automates various marketing processes and enhances brand experience. The company provides tools for creating a wide range of content, including blog posts, social media updates, and marketing copy, leveraging advanced AI technology. It features a text-to-image generator that allows users to create visually appealing, on-brand images based on textual descriptions.
short_description: Jasper is an AI platform specifically designed for marketing, enabling users to generate high-quality content.

name: Breeze Airways
description:
Breeze Airways is a new airline that builds something brand new and really special for guests. Breeze Airways (initially Moxy Airways) is a planned airline in the United States due to begin operations in 2021. 

The airline was founded by David Neeleman (who previously co-founded Morris Air, WestJet, JetBlue, and Azul Linhas Aereas).
short_description: Breeze Airways is a new airline that builds something brand new and really special for guests.

name: Avalanche
description: Avalanche is an open, programmable smart contracts platform for decentralized applications. Avalanche is a verifiable platform for institutions, enterprises, and governments. Launch assets, build applications and create subnets with complete control over your implementation with compliance, data security, and other rulesets built into the foundation.
short_description: Avalanche provides a decentralized contracts platform for global finance, with near-instant transaction completion.

name: Magic
description: Magic is a wallet-as-a-service provider that helps businesses onboard users into web3 with instant non-custodial wallet creation. It uses email or social logins, while removing the need for seed phrases and browser extensions - making it indistinguishable from standard web2 experiences that everyday users are accustomed to. Magic offers features for end-to-end web3 onboarding including authentication, fiat onramps, NFT Minting and NFT Checkout. Its solutions are trusted by top brands in web2 and web3, including Mattel, Macy's, Xsolla, Immutable, and more. The company's solution makes use of a plug-and-play kit and blockchain infrastructure to enable individuals to build applications with quick, customized, password-less login with just a few lines of code, allowing developers to include password-less authentication in their applications.
short_description: Magic is a developer of SDK that integrates with applications to enable password-less Web3 onboarding and authentication.

name: Brightline
description:
Brightline is a technology-enabled behavioral health home for children and their families. Brightline delivers integrated care through innovative technology, virtual behavioral health services, and a collaborative care team focused on supporting children across developmental stages and their families.

The company was founded in 2019 and is based in Palo Alto, California.
short_description: Brightline is a med-tech company that provides behavioral healthcare services for children and their families.
categories: Child Care,Family,Health Care,Home Health Care,Mental Health

name: Arya Health
description: Arya Health is a healthcare technology firm dedicated to improving healthcare workforce management with AI-powered automation.
short_description: Arya Health is a healthcare technology firm dedicated to improving healthcare workforce management with AI-powered automation.

name: Wellgistics Health
description: Wellgistics Health is a healthcare technology and pharmaceutical logistics company that streamlines prescription fulfillment through an integrated technology platform, wholesale distribution, and a fulfillment network, primarily serving independent pharmacies and specialty medications. Wellgistics Health offers services such as prior authorization assistance, clinical concierge support, and patient adherence tools.
short_description: Wellgistics Health is a logistic company that focuses on streamlining healthcare technology and pharmaceutical from manufacturer to patient.

name: Procurement Sciences AI
description: Procurement Sciences develops an AI-powered software platform tailored to businesses that pursue government contracts. The company's flagship product, Awarded AI, is built to manage the entire contract lifecycle: from identifying public-sector opportunities to producing proposals, ensuring compliance and supporting contract delivery With features like AI-powered opportunity search, advanced proposal generation, and compliance checking, Awarded AI empowers contractors to enhance efficiency and win rates.
short_description: Procurement Sciences develops an AI-powered software platform tailored to businesses that pursue government contracts.

name: Rillet
description: Rillet is an AI-native ERP that automates accounting for complex revenue models, allowing for fast book closings and providing a reliable source of truth. The solution covers the full spectrum of accounting and finance needs, including customer invoicing, GAAP-compliant revenue recognition, automated bank reconciliations, accrual-based expense recognition, real-time SaaS metrics, and other analytics capabilities. Rillet covers multiple entities, geographies, and currencies and allows for consolidated multi-currency reportin,g all embedded within one platform.
short_description: Rillet is an AI-native ERP platform that automates accounting for complex revenue models.

name: Ramp
description: Ramp provides a unified finance operations platform that includes corporate cards, expense tracking, bill payments, vendor and procurement workflows, travel management, and automated accounting. The platform embeds policy controls, approval workflows, and real‑time alerts to manage spending proactively, helping finance teams reduce manual tasks and improve visibility. It integrates with ERP and HRIS systems, syncs transactions reliably, and supports global operations across multiple currencies. Leveraging AI, Ramp automates expense submission, invoice processing, data coding, and cost‑saving insights. Businesses report accelerated month‑end closing, fewer errors, and more transparent spending with the platform.
short_description: Ramp is a financial operations platform designed to save companies time and money

name: Upwind Security
description: Upwind Security develops cybersecurity tools to help organizations protect their digital assets. It identifies potential threats for data integrity. It provides security measures and support compliance.
short_description: Upwind Security provides cybersecurity solutions to protect organizations from digital threats and vulnerabilities.

name: TaxBit
description:
TaxBit is a cryptocurrency tax and accounting software that automates tax calculations and reports on cryptocurrency transactions. With TaxBit, users can link their exchanges and wallets to seamlessly pull their transactions through their tax engine and auto-generate tax forms.

Aside from automating taxes, TaxBit provides crypto enthusiasts with real-time portfolio tracking and tax optimization visibility so that they can make tax-optimized crypto trades throughout the year. TaxBit connects the consumer and enterprise cryptocurrency tax experiences.
short_description: TaxBit is a cryptocurrency tax and accounting software that automates tax calculations and reporting on cryptocurrency transactions.

name: LEXEO Therapeutics
description: LEXEO Therapeutics is a fully integrated biotechnology company.  LEXEO Therapeutics’ pipeline consists of adeno-associated virus (AAV)-mediated therapies primarily developed at Weill Cornell Medicine’s Department of Genetic Medicine. Beyond LEXEO Therapeutics’ lead programs – which are focused on both rare and non-rare monogenic (single gene mutation) diseases – the company’s preclinical pipeline spans monogenic diseases, as well as hereditary and acquired diseases across a spectrum of patient population sizes and a range of unmet medical needs. Importantly, LEXEO Therapeutics will focus on advancing clinical programs through to commercialization, with the goal of maintaining an ongoing research collaboration with Weill Cornell Medicine’s Department of Genetic Medicine to help advance the company’s pre-clinical pipeline.
short_description: LEXEO Therapeutics utilizes gene therapy to treat genetically defined cardiovascular and central nervous system diseases.

name: Audioshake
description: Audioshake makes sound more usable for both humans and machines by separating sound into its component parts. Used by some the world's largest media, entertainment, and tech companies, AudioShake is used in audio editing workflows, Voice AI, and multimodal training.
short_description: Audioshake makes audio more usable for both humans and machines by separating sound into its different component parts.

name: Alternative Payments
description: Alternative Payments is the platform that accelerates cash flow and boosts revenue without traditional payment complexities.
short_description: Alternative Payments is the platform that accelerates cash flow and boosts revenue without traditional payment complexities.

name: Routefusion
description: Routefusion offers tools and infrastructure for cross-border payments and banking services. It enables businesses to manage international payouts and collections via a unified API that supports virtual accounts, SWIFT transfers, and local or real-time payment rails. The platform provides white-label payout solutions and handles compliance and currency conversions. Routefusion assists companies in integrating global financial operations into their products and workflows with flexibility and automation.
short_description: Routefusion is a financial infrastructure company that specializes in cross-border payments and remittances.

name: TransCrypts
description: TransCrypts is a tool for Human Resource Departments to automate the issuance of employment and income verification documents using the blockchain. Our proprietary process not only saves HRs time, money, and headache in dealing with compliance but also gives employees total control over how their work information is being shared.
short_description: TransCrypts is a SaaS company that offers consumer empowered record management services.

name: CodeRabbit
description: CodeRabbit offers software tools that perform automated code reviews using artificial intelligence. It inspects pull requests line by line, checks code flow and logic, enforces coding standards, runs linters and static analysis, and provides summaries of changes. It integrates with platforms like GitHub, GitLab, or Azure DevOps, and allows configuration with issue trackers such as Jira or Linear. It secures code reviews through encrypted data transmission and makes review feedback available in IDEs or via CLI. It includes features like autogenerated release notes, sprint reports, and support for both SaaS and self-hosted deployments.
short_description: CodeRabbit offers software tools that perform automated code reviews using artificial intelligence.

name: Sola
description: Sola supports teams focused on automation by helping them create robotic agents proficient in managing repetitive tasks through the use of Large Language Models (LLMs) and computer vision. Sola supports companies across legal, financial, insurance, and healthcare, enabling citizen developers for their teams and process mining their existing workflow.
short_description: Sola assists automation-minded companies in building robotic agents that are capable of handling tedious tasks via LLMs and computer vision.
categories: Artificial Intelligence (AI),Business Process Automation (BPA),Data Center Automation,Machine Learning,Robotics

name: Eleos Health
description: Eleos Health provides automated health tech solutions that accelerate clinicians’ decision-making via an AI-powered Speech-to-Insights system to ensure the provision of personalized and time and cost-effective care.
short_description: Eleos Health is a mental health startup that focuses on using voice analysis and NLP to improve treatment outcomes and workflow efficiency.

name: Unstoppable Domains
description: Unstoppable Domains launches domains secured by blockchains and builds uncensorable websites. The company offers NFT domains that give people control of their digital identity. Its usernames can be used to log into more than 150 Web3 applications, shorten crypto wallet addresses, and build a decentralized Web3 identity.
short_description: Unstoppable Domains launches domains secured by blockchains and builds uncensorable websites.

name: Angel Studios
description: Angel Studios is a video streaming service and media company that finances its productions through equity crowdfunding. They are a film studio platform that enables creators and viewers to collaborate to produce high-calibre television and film without having to answer to Hollywood.
short_description: Angel Studios is a video streaming service and media company that finances its productions through equity crowdfunding.
categories: Digital Entertainment,Film Production,Financial Services,Media and Entertainment,TV Production,Video Streaming

name: Invivyd
description: Invivyd is a commercial-stage biopharmaceutical company that delivers protection from serious viral infectious diseases. It is on a mission to rapidly and perpetually deliver antibody-based therapies that protect vulnerable people from the devastating consequences of circulating viral threats, beginning with SARS-CoV-2.
short_description: Invivyd develops antibodies to transcend the limitations of the human immune system and fight against viral infections.

name: Distyl AI
description: Distyl AI delivers platforms and services that embed artificial intelligence into enterprise operations to generate measurable business outcomes. It offers a platform (“Distillery Platform”) that enables companies to deploy and manage AI systems rapidly, integrating directly with data, workflows, and existing enterprise infrastructure. Custom research, systems optimization, and deep technical deployment are part of its capabilities, with engineering and strategy contribution from teams with backgrounds in major institutions like OpenAI, Apple, and Palantir. Distyl AI works with clients across sectors such as healthcare, telecom, manufacturing, insurance, and retail to create AI-driven solutions tied to financial or operational impact.
short_description: Distyl AI specializes in providing artificial intelligence solutions tailored for large enterprises.

name: Digits
description: Digits is a fintech company building tools for businesses and finance professionals by leveraging its proprietary Living Model technology. The company was founded by Wayne Chang and Jeff Seibert in 2018 and is headquartered in San Francisco, California, United States.
short_description: Digits is a fintech company that offers financial tools for small businesses.

name: EVEN
description: EVEN is the leading direct-to-fan superfan platform empowering artists, creators, and labels to sell music and unique fan experiences directly to their audiences before they hit streaming services. As the first and only superfan platform accredited by Luminate to report sales directly to Billboard charts, EVEN integrates seamlessly with major distributors, labels, and industry partners, automating onboarding and unlocking powerful monetization through custom releases, livestreams, exclusive content, and community-building tools.

name: Webull Corporation
description:
Webull Corporation is the parent company of the Webull Group, which owns and operates the popular Webull online trading platform. As of November 2024, the Webull Group operates in 15 regions globally and is backed by private equity investors located in the United States, Europe and Asia. Webull serves more than 20 million registered users globally, providing retail investors with 24/7 access to global financial markets. Users can put investment strategies to work by trading global stocks, ETFs, options, futures and fractional shares through Webull's trading platform, which seamlessly integrates market data and information, its user community, and investor education resources.

Webull began in 2016 in the city of Changsha, China, as a free app aggregating market data for users globally. Users of the Webull app mostly used it to obtain market data for their personal investment strategies and then executed those strategies on other brokerage platforms. Webull established Webull Financial LLC on May 24, 2017, to be a licensed broker-dealer in the U.S., allowing its users to execute their investment strategies directly on the Webull platform. FINRA approved Webull to operate as a broker in the U.S. on January 4, 2018. As the Webull platform grew, Webull sought diversified investments to continue its expansion in the U.S. and globally. To facilitate investments from global investors and an eventual listing on a global stock exchange, on September 2, 2019, Webull Corporation was established to as the ultimate parent and holding company for Webull’s global business.

Webull continues to expand by adding new entities in new markets. Due to the nature of the brokerage business, every market in which Webull operates requires it to establish a local entity and apply for a brokerage license from the securities regulators in that jurisdiction. As a result, the Webull Group now consists of Webull Corporation and numerous local holding and operating entities across 15 different markets.
short_description: Webull Corporation is a technology-driven financial services company

name: Cellares
description:
Cellares develops the Cell Shuttle, to overcome the challenges associated with manufacturing so these life-saving therapies are affordable and widely available to patients who can benefit.

The clinical impact of cell therapy in treating cancer has been proven, but this therapeutic approach has several limitations, especially in manufacturing, leaving extremely sick patients waiting for treatment and desperate for hope.
Since cell therapy is currently produced for a single patient at a time, it is expensive to manufacture, requiring significant time and resources, and is difficult to scale. 

Preclinical and clinical scientists, as well as commercial cell therapy manufacturers also lack the options to fully automate their manufacturing process quickly, safely, cost-effectively, and at the scale they need.

The Cell Shuttle is an automated and closed end-to-end manufacturing solution that is flexible and scalable, enabling customers to run exact processes specified for their cell therapy. Compared with the current manual manufacturing processes for cell therapy, the Cell Shuttle’s next-generation automated manufacturing solution has 10 times the scalability (meaning 10 times more patient doses can be produced simultaneously), enables a three-fold reduction in process failure rates, and will reduce the per-patient manufacturing cost by up to 70 percent for most processes.
short_description: Cellares is a life sciences technology company that develops the Cell Shuttle to automate cell therapy manufacturing.

At Prometheus Hyperscale, we believe in creating data centers that are both environmentally friendly and incredibly powerful. Our hyperscale data centers prioritize the migration to renewable energy sources and next-generation advanced nuclear, significantly reducing our environmental impact while delivering unparalleled computing efficiency.

Our mission extends beyond technological innovation; we are equally committed to making high-performance computing accessible and advantageous for the broader society. Our facilities are not just centers of technological excellence but also contribute positively to local communities by offering employment opportunities, heat reuse host products, and other economic and societal benefits.

The strategic positioning of our data centers in Wyoming offers distinct advantages. The cooler climate facilitates natural cooling for adjacent data center clusters, access to renewable energy sources is readily available, and the regulatory environment is supportive of our innovative initiatives. These factors, combined with our cutting-edge approach to data center design and management, establish Prometheus Hyperscale as a vanguard in the evolution of data infrastructure.

Prometheus Hyperscale stands as a symbol of technological advancement and an embodiment of the potential of human creativity in leveraging technology for the greater good of society.

name: Webull
description:
Webull Corporation is the parent company of the Webull Group, which owns and operates the popular Webull online trading platform. As of November 2024, the Webull Group operates in 15 regions globally and is backed by private equity investors located in the United States, Europe and Asia. Webull serves more than 20 million registered users globally, providing retail investors with 24/7 access to global financial markets. Users can put investment strategies to work by trading global stocks, ETFs, options, futures and fractional shares through Webull's trading platform, which seamlessly integrates market data and information, its user community, and investor education resources.

Webull began in 2016 in the city of Changsha, China, as a free app aggregating market data for users globally. Users of the Webull app mostly used it to obtain market data for their personal investment strategies and then executed those strategies on other brokerage platforms. Webull established Webull Financial LLC on May 24, 2017, to be a licensed broker-dealer in the U.S., allowing its users to execute their investment strategies directly on the Webull platform. FINRA approved Webull to operate as a broker in the U.S. on January 4, 2018. As the Webull platform grew, Webull sought diversified investments to continue its expansion in the U.S. and globally. To facilitate investments from global investors and an eventual listing on a global stock exchange, on September 2, 2019, Webull Corporation was established to as the ultimate parent and holding company for Webull’s global business.

Webull continues to expand by adding new entities in new markets. Due to the nature of the brokerage business, every market in which Webull operates requires it to establish a local entity and apply for a brokerage license from the securities regulators in that jurisdiction. As a result, the Webull Group now consists of Webull Corporation and numerous local holding and operating entities across 15 different markets.
short_description: Webull is a stock trading mobile application that features commission-free stock and exchange-traded fund (ETF) trading.

Key Features:

MedPass: AI-powered fast enrollments.
PolicyNest CRM: Optimizes agent and customer interactions.
HealthBird Clinics Integration: Seamless healthcare services.
Enterprise Solutions: Custom partnerships, including recent expansion into Ecuador, Mexico and El Salvador.

Where Does HealthBird Operate?
Primarily U.S.-based with growing international reach, HealthBird adapts its platform to meet regional needs and regulatory requirements, enabling partnerships with governments and organizations worldwide.

Part of OneNest
Now under the OneNest umbrella, HealthBird benefits from shared resources, expanded global reach, and integration with complementary brands like CareBird and TravelBird. This synergy enhances its ability to deliver accessible, innovative healthcare solutions.

Mission
HealthBird and OneNest share a vision of revolutionizing healthcare through technology, making high-quality, user-friendly solutions the standard for individuals and organizations alike.

Founded in 2011 and listed on Nasdaq in May 2025, iQSTEL has demonstrated exponential growth, with 2024 revenue up 95.9% to $283.2M and a 2025 target of $340M. Strategic acquisitions—like the recent integration of Globetopper—are expected to push annual revenue beyond $400M. The company is on track for $1B by 2027, supported by a high-margin, scalable model and a $1M cost-saving initiative. With over 400 interconnections, advanced AI platforms, and expanding fintech and cybersecurity offerings, iQSTEL is building a diversified, future-proof tech powerhouse that aims to make high-tech tools globally accessible.

name: GEODNET
description:
The Global Earth Observation Decentralized Network (GEODNET) is a decentralized network of Space Weather mining stations that report the real-time influence of the Sun’s solar winds on the Global Navigation Satellite System (GNSS) signals. This data is commonly used to accurately correct GNSS (GPS and other navigation satellite) signals to provide centimeter level positioning accuracy and improve absolute time accuracy to nano-second level. Traditional applications for these data services include Automotive/Autonomous Navigation, Agriculture/Construction Vehicle Machine Control, Earthquake/Geohazard Monitoring, and traditional Land Survey. Blockchain applications include decentralized Mapping, Metaverse Digital Twins, Location-Aware Smart Contracts, and Proof-of-Location and Time.
GEOD is the native utility token that is used for: Fees for providing GEODNET data streams and services. Rewards to Space Weather Miners. Used for governance votes to determine how network resources are allocated. Gas for future native GEODNET blockchain location/time proofs.
short_description: Global Earth Observation Decentralized Network (GEODNET) is the first network that utilizes the limited Earth surface as the resource.

name: Leantime
description:
TLDR: Leantime is a project management app that helps non-project managers at both enterprises and SMBs to easily connect strategy to their day-to-day execution while maintaining employee engagement through the use of behavioral science, motivational psychology and AI.

Project management that people actually want to use.

Taking a big picture view on the experience we have in working, Leantime steps away from the traditional approaches of task management and seeks to solve a bigger issue: How do we stay engaged and consistent with the purpose and value of our work? 

Adoption of PM tools is often cumbersome and most people have a love-hate relationship with their tools. By incorporating AI and principles of neuroscience & behavioral science, Leantime works to make the work that a user is doing personal, easy (don't have to figure out workflows), goal focused and engaging. 

Some of our features include:
- Kanban, List, & Table views for To Dos
- Subtasks & Dependencies with a visual Kanban overview
- Goals
- Idea Management
- Milestones
- Strategy Boards (SWOT, Business Model Canvas, Lean, +more)
- High level strategic one pager 
- Timesheets and time tracking 
- Reports & Analytics
- Retrospectives / Project reviews
- Portfolio overview
- Document & File management
- ADHD friendly & inclusive reading themes
- And more

Now available in cloud:
AI Beta (reach out if interested!)
Program Management
Strategy Management 2.0

Leantime went open source in 2019 and has grown to one of the top open source project management systems (and the prettiest one, according to our users!) with over 50,000 downloads and an active discord & open source community. 

Leantime has been part of the AWS Impact Accelerator Latino Founders Cohort 2023, an NC IDEA MICRO grant recipient, a NC IDEA Seed semi-finalist, a RIoT accelerator participant, a NC Tech Top 10 NC Tech Startups to Watch in 2023, and is a Techstars portfolio company.
short_description: Leantime is an open source project management system for non-project managers using behavioral science and AI to make work engaging.

name: Zulu Pods
description: Zulu Pods is a groundbreaking fluid delivery technology company focusing on dual-use applications in defense and aerospace markets.  The ZPod is a first-of-its-kind technology that revolutionizes fluid delivery by unitizing traditional circulating systems that typically rely on a network of tanks, pumps, nozzles, plumbing, etc., to move fluid from point A to point B within a mechanical system.  The ZPod lowers part count, lowers weight and cost, while also increasing performance on expendable and attritable platforms.  The Zulu Pods technology stack is also being applied to increase safety margin for helicopters during loss of lubrication events.  Finally, Zulu Pods is fielding a new and fully automated device, called the Anti-Corrosion SmartPod (ACSP) that simplifies routine maintenance of any oil-wetted assets.  A shop tool that simply interfaces with any asset and provides on-time routine lubrication while constantly assessing the health of the asset and its environment.  The ACSP's debut will be deployed on the F-35B in collaboration with Rolls-Royce and the F-35 Joint Program Office.
short_description: Zulu Pods is a dual-use defense and aerospace fluid delivery technology company based out of South Florida and Western Massachusetts.

name: Destiny (D/XYZ)
description:
Over the last decade, we have spent our lives living and breathing the silicon valley start-up life. From coding in our living room to enacting hundred-million-dollar acquisitions, we came to Silicon Valley with a vision. We envisioned a future that many wrote off as unnecessary, but today is the inevitable future of the private market economy.

But while we have thrived from the unparalleled growth and opportunity in the private market, the rest of the world has not. Instead, our friends and family stand outside, looking in as class divisions have widened, and a sense of inequality has become pervasive.

In this time of growth — this era of technological wonder, innovation, and entrepreneurship — how can we do better? How can we scale the most significant opportunity of our generation? By providing public access to the private market.

As a society, we must make innovation accessible, because making sure that the next generation of innovators can have ownership of the future is the first step in inspiring them to take ownership of the future.

Invest in access for everyone, invest in shared future, invest in progress.
D/XYZ is a future for everyone.
Own a piece of the future, today.
short_description: Destiny XYZ is an Investment Management firm offering Public Access to Private Tech.

name: Celer Network
description:
Celer Network is a technology and economic architecture enabling high scalability of public blockchains with off-chain scaling approaches.

Existing payment network proposals and implementations do not have a clear separation between functional components. This tight coupling poses significant challenges for protocol evolution, because changing one requires changes to the whole stack all the way to the applications. Celer Network draws inspiration from the success of layered network architecture from the Internet and push for a clean abstraction of a four-layered payment network architecture consisting of Channel Management, Payment Routing, Payment Transport and Application Runtime. This architecture enables flexibility and more importantly, independent, and fast evolution on each layer. Within this clean network architecture, Celer Network provides innovative solutions on all layers, with highlights of cChannel, cRoute and cOS .
short_description: Celer Network is an inter-blockchain and cross-layer communication platform.

name: Clean Earth Rovers
description:
Ports, rivers, beaches, and harbors are polluted. Over 50% are considered impaired (not safe for routine use) as a result of misplaced debris, oil spills, bacteria presence, and industrial runoff. Maritime stakeholders both monitor the condition and health of their waters by hand, and clean adverse pollutants by hand. We automate this process from start to finish.

Our DataPod™ smart buoy unlocks scalable real time water quality data infrastructure. This provides stakeholders with risk reports and acts as a canary in a coal mine for pending pollution threats. Our Gilligan AI™ also helps users analyze their data, forecast future conditions, and take action.

We don't just stop at telling you there's a problem, our Rover AVPro autonomously skims oil, algae, dead-fish, and marine debris from coastal waterways. This allows stakeholders to focus on the task at hand, automate their operation, and increase their efficiency and safety of remediation and cleanup efforts. 

Clean Earth Rovers is deployed nationally in Florida, Ohio, and California.
short_description: We automate harbor pollution management with scalable smart buoys and "Roombas" for the water

name: Soteri Skin
description:
Company Overview: Soteri Skin Inc. is a clinically tested, consumer skin health start-up that has participated in both the YC accelerator program (W22) and Harvard Innovation Labs.
At Soteri Skin, we are revolutionizing treatments for Atopic Dermatitis (eczema) with our patented technology, trademarked as Soteri Skin’s signature pH/LOCK™ complex. This innovative approach offers an outside-in pathway to treating eczema by repairing the skin barrier. It accomplishes this by restoring the skin's acid mantle, and correcting the skin pH to an optimal level of 4.7 for a full 12 hours. This creates an ideal environment for skin renewal and supports a healthy skin microbiome, both essential for repairing the skin barrier. A stronger, more resilient skin barrier prevents allergens, pathogens, and harmful bacteria from penetrating the skin and causing inflammation while locking in moisture.

name: Eqvista
description:
Eqvista is a comprehensive equity management platform that revolutionizes private market infrastructure with our breakthrough Eqvista Real-Time Company Valuation® technology, combining expert valuations from our in-house team of NACVA-certified, CVA and CFA analysts to eliminate traditional valuation delays that constrain strategic decisions and market efficiency.

With over $200 billion in equity valued across diverse clients from pre-seed startups to unicorns and VCs, we've built the pricing transparency infrastructure that private markets require. Our credentialed team processes $5B in monthly valuations while maintaining institutional-grade quality standards backed by professional certifications including Certified Valuation Analyst (CVA) and Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA).

As industry leaders in 409A valuations, we provide audit-defensible assessments signed by our CVA and CFA analysts, with lifetime audit support and full IRS defense backed by our Enrolled Agent status. Founded to solve the fundamental problem of pricing delays in private markets, Eqvista is creating the infrastructure foundation that enables efficient private market operations. We're building toward institutional-scale adoption while serving the full spectrum from early-stage startups through pre-IPO enterprises.

Introducing Eqvista Real-Time Company Valuation®

Traditional valuations require waiting weeks for reports that quickly become obsolete. Our innovative Eqvista Real-Time Company Valuation® feature transforms this by maintaining current fair market value as businesses evolve, enabling strategic decisions at market speed rather than administrative timelines.

All-in-one Platform 

Our comprehensive platform serves the complete equity lifecycle - from initial stock issuances and advanced vesting configurations to employee option programs, fundraising rounds, and M&A transactions. We handle all equity types including common stock, preferred shares, RSUs, warrants, and convertible securities with integrated compliance for ASC 718, 83(b) elections, and specialized services like QSBS attestation.
short_description: Manage your company’s cap table and valuations with Eqvista!

With the wake word “Hey Goldsainte,” users can engage a conversational concierge to search, plan, and book flights, hotels, dining, events, and transportation—completely hands-free and in real time.

At the core of the platform is a travel agent marketplace where users can post complex itineraries, receive competitive bids from certified agents, and pay securely through milestone-based transactions. The system supports group bookings, split payments, full itinerary management, and real-time messaging, making it easy to coordinate even the most intricate trips.

Goldsainte also powers a unique creator economy: content creators collaborate with agents to co-build and promote curated travel experiences, while transportation vendors can onboard, promote their services, and be included in creator or agent-led packages. This three-sided ecosystem—AI + Agents + Creators—makes Goldsainte the first platform to unify inspiration, planning, and booking within one intelligent, social commerce environment.

This is not just a solution; it's a commitment to a greener future. By enhancing the remaining useful life of lithium-ion batteries, we are reducing the demand for foreign energy, bolstering national energy security and slashing carbon emissions. Our method is a blueprint for environmental stewardship, ensuring that lithium batteries contribute to a clean energy ecosystem rather than becoming a part of the problem.

Higher Wire is not only a technology company; we are also an ethical enterprise, keen on making energy solutions that are both sustainable and accessible. We pride ourselves on creating carbon-negative energy storage solutions through a green renewal process us in powering the future responsibly.

That's why we've created this website as a resource to provide accurate and up-to-date information on the latest news and changes in US immigration policy.

Our team of experts is dedicated to providing valuable insights and guidance on topics such as visas, green cards, citizenship, naturalization, and more. We also provide helpful tips and advice on navigating the US immigration system, including the application process, interview preparation, and working with immigration officials.

name: Urgently Health
description:
Unexpected medical care is stressful enough for patients and healthcare providers, so Urgently Health strives to streamline and simplify the last-minute, unplanned medical process.

Our mobile application (Urgently Health), available for both Apple and Android devices, allows patients to discover local, available, medical care facilities based on their specific medical needs, along with estimated wait times so they can be seen and treated as soon as possible.

The App also allows patients to browse providers based on specialties and services offered, as well as by insurances accepted. This way, patients avoid surprises when arriving at the front desk.

Additional patient benefits include:
-- Filling out paperwork before arriving at urgent care facilities, hospitals, and other walk-in medical providers
-- Seeing medical care facility information, including locations, hours of operation, estimated wait times, contact information, specialties and services offered, and insurances accepted
-- Storage of their medical forms, medical history, pre-existing conditions, etc.
-- Reduction of wait times in hospitals, clinics, emergency rooms, and other medical care providers
-- Reduction of stress associated with unplanned, last-minute care and medical emergencies

Urgently Health also notifies the hospital or clinic a patient chooses that they are on their way to them, providing healthcare facilities with an approximate travel time. This feature allows providers to expect patients and better prepare for their arrival before they get there. This is vitally important during emergencies where mere minutes can make a difference!

Our accompanying Web Platform allows hospitals and clinics who accept walk-in patients to process them more effectively and with less confusion than in the past. When healthcare facilities use our Platform, they expand their visibility and streamline their day-to-day operations. This, in turn, increases their preparedness and allows them to discover and overcome bottlenecks, leading to more effective and efficient service, greater patient satisfaction and retention, and decreased costs.

With patient information on-hand before they arrive, providers can assign severity, pre-triage, and verify information before their patients arrive. The Platform also provides healthcare administrators with statistics such as hot-times, most common ailments, and historical wait-times to mitigate over and under-staffing and ensure preparation.
short_description: Humanizing Healthcare
categories: Android,Electronic Health Record (EHR),Emergency Medicine,Health Care,Hospital,iOS,mHealth,Mobile,Mobile Apps

As your local weed plug, we’re everything your old plug wasn’t – quick, consistent, and always stocked. Whether you’re vibing with one-on-one in-store recommendations, rolling through curbside pickup, or keeping it low-key with delivery, we make getting what you need effortless. 
But JARS is more than just a dispensary. We’re here to reshape the culture and push the industry forward. Our roots run deep in the communities we serve, and every move we make is about breaking barriers, giving back, and building real connections that matter. This isn’t just about cannabis. name: Nibav Home Lifts Inc.
description:
Nibav Lifts Inc., a premier elevator brand and manufacturer, leads in air-driven lift technology, offering a wide range of eco-friendly, pneumatic vacuum elevators across 12+ countries with 40+ experience centers. Our innovative, machine room-less elevators, notable for their small footprint and high quality, provide a luxurious, wheelchair-accessible alternative to stair lifts. Dedicated to elevator modernization, we ensure ultimate comfort and style for homes in the United States and beyond, redefining home mobility with efficiency and elegance.
We lead in innovative Home lift technology, ensuring our air-driven home lifts are designed with your convenience in mind, offering a seamless and effortless experience that transforms your daily life. Compliance with rigorous international safety standards is central to our mission. We prioritize the well-being of our customers, ensuring that our air-powered home lift system adheres to the highest safety measures. Bid farewell to traditional elevators and welcome the future of vertical mobility into your home with our cutting-edge solutions.

Mission
At Nibav Lifts Inc, we revolutionize residential mobility with cutting-edge, affordable, and eco-friendly home lifts. Committed to enhancing life quality and property value, our focus on excellence and affordability sets new industry benchmarks. Our expert engineers drive innovation in vertical mobility technology. As a global industry entity, we cater to diverse homeowner needs, making living spaces inclusive and convenient. Join us for an accessible and technologically advanced living environment, experiencing the future of residential mobility.

Vision
At Nibav Lifts Inc, our vision is to be a global leader in the home lift sector, renowned for technological prowess, exceptional craftsmanship, and customer satisfaction. We strive for innovation, pushing boundaries to evolve and perfect lifts based on changing needs. Prioritizing sustainability and efficiency, we aim to contribute to an accessible and environmentally conscious future. Our focus on empowering individuals facing mobility challenges aligns with our commitment to enhance overall well-being.

Story
With a strong global presence in 12+ countries and 40+ experience centers, including the US, we envision the future with dedication to innovation. Continuously refining our lifts to meet evolving needs, Nibav Home Lifts stands as a beacon for cutting-edge solutions. Join us in shaping an accessible and environmentally conscious world. Our story centers on empowerment, enabling individuals with mobility challenges to move freely within their homes, enhancing overall well-being. Nibav Lifts Inc isn’t just a company; it’s a journey towards a more inclusive and sustainable tomorrow.
Expertise and Experience
The experience and the expertise we show in the industry have lifted us to the throne of being the most trusted provider of residential lifts. Nibav Home Lifts’ in its extensive reach to the world’s most advanced and efficient home lifts offers models that can be optimized to fit your needs and style. Our European standard of safety guidelines is meticulously followed throughout the process of production gaining us the prestigious ISO9001 certifications. We take pride in providing aesthetically pleasing, and compact home elevators that take every individual into consideration, delivering seamless mobility solutions, globally. Furthermore, our all-encompassing showrooms, and experience centers in the US, stand testament to our goal projected firsthand to the world.

Certified Quality: European Excellence, ISO9001 Compliance

Sustainability and Innovation
Building and crafting environmentally friendly products are in high demand, and we are no exception to the list. Our home lifts bridge the gap between innovation and sustainability, which utilizing air pressure to mobilize the product. This not only significantly reduces the carbon footprint but also exemplifies our commitment to pushing the boundaries of unique designs. Our approach involves seamlessly integrating leading-edge technology with robust, fail-safe safety mechanisms. Nibav Home Lifts offers a compact cabin with a range of sizes, including wheelchair accessibility catering to the diverse needs of our customers. We discover and elevate your everyday vertical mobility experience to a scenic adventure in the most efficient way!
short_description: The Home Elevator Company

name: ShyftOff

ShyftOff is revolutionizing how contact centers staff.

We're helping centers adapt to agents' demands for flexibility, where 40-year best practices now fall short. We killed 8-hour schedules, mandatory OT, commuting, and low-income wages.

We built a flexible contact center, designed for a flexible and modern workforce. We made it possible for brands, and even BPOs, to pay competitively, even as wages increase. Imagine the CX professionals you'd attract with flexibility and higher pay!

And contact centers are better when they're flexible...

ShyftOff helps CX teams staff perfectly as volume fluctuates throughout the days, weeks, months, or seasons. Flexible teams can even surge up for the unexpected.

ShyftOff also helps combat rising costs of customer service. A productive hour pricing model saves 35%+ by eliminating shrinkage and stabilizing occupancy. 

We're not a BPO, but we partner like one. We're a tech company and strategic partner helping CX teams operate in a modern economy and workforce.
